-- SAP wants to add Ariba CEO to management board
-- 
-- Tue May 22, 2012 5:21pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/05/22/us-sap-ariba-idUSBRE84L1AF20120522

 

 FRANKFURT  (Reuters) - SAP said on Tuesday it wanted to add Ariba's Chief Executive Bob Calderoni to the German business software maker's global managing board after closing the $4.3 billion deal. 
 The company expects to close the acquisition in the third quarter and the transaction is expected to be accretive to SAP's earnings per share in 2013. (Reporting by Harro ten Wolde)